</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1772,1941]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Large to very large species (
<quantity box="[465,591,1773,1797]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="13.0">13–22 mm</quantity>
), body black, elytra with bluish reflections, abdomen black at most with the tip reddish (
<figureCitation box="[287,386,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 124 – 129. 124, 125" captionStartId="51.[151,264,1809,1831]" captionTargetBox="[170,1415,318,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[150,1437,301,1751]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURES 124 – 129. 124, 125, Thyreocephalus michaeli Janák; 126, 127, T. ferox (Harold); 128, 129, T. raptor Tottenham; 124, 126, 128, habitus; 125, 127, 129, head. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289905/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[340,386,1809,1833]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="128.0">128</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head very densely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[735,843,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 124 – 129. 124, 125" captionStartId="51.[151,264,1809,1831]" captionTargetBox="[170,1415,318,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[150,1437,301,1751]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURES 124 – 129. 124, 125, Thyreocephalus michaeli Janák; 126, 127, T. ferox (Harold); 128, 129, T. raptor Tottenham; 124, 126, 128, habitus; 125, 127, 129, head. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289905/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Figs. 
<number box="[799,843,1809,1833]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1.29153158E8">129</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[856,900,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 153 – 157" captionStartId="62.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[185,1399,209,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@62.[172,1416,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURES 153 – 157. Thyreocephalus basilewskyi Cameron; 153, head and pronotum; 154, labrum; 155, male tergite 10; 156, male sternite 9; 157, aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289913/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">153</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[913,958,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 158 – 165" captionStartId="64.[151,264,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,206,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@64.[151,1436,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 158 – 165. Thyreocephalus interocularis (Eppelsheim); 158, head and pronotum (iop—interior ocular puncture, pop—postocular punctures); 159, labrum; 160, male tergite 10; 161, male sternite 9; 162, aedeagus; 163, 164, median lobe (extreme shapes); 165, paramere (extreme shape)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289914/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">158</figureCitation>
), with interior ocular puncture situated far from inner margin of eye, ocular groove between interior ocular puncture and inner border of eye shallow, but in general distinct, transverse or slightly oblique, temples with two large setiferous postocular puncture, labrum slightly lobate (
<figureCitation box="[325,433,1916,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 142 – 146" captionStartId="58.[151,264,1970,1992]" captionTargetBox="[231,1362,208,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@58.[212,1374,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 142 – 146. Thyreocephalus subcorticalis sp. nov.; 142, head and pronotum; 143, labrum; 144, male tergite 10; 145, male sternite 9; 146, aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289910/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Figs. 
<number box="[389,433,1917,1941]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1.43149154159E11">143</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[445,489,1917,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 148 – 152" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1974,1996]" captionTargetBox="[221,1379,201,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[198,1389,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 148 – 152. Thyreocephalus raptor Tottenham; 148, head and pronotum; 149, labrum; 150, male tergite 10; 151, male sternite 9; 152, aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289912/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">149</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[501,545,1916,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 153 – 157" captionStartId="62.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[185,1399,209,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@62.[172,1416,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURES 153 – 157. Thyreocephalus basilewskyi Cameron; 153, head and pronotum; 154, labrum; 155, male tergite 10; 156, male sternite 9; 157, aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289913/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">154</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[557,603,1916,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 158 – 165" captionStartId="64.[151,264,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,206,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@64.[151,1436,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 158 – 165. Thyreocephalus interocularis (Eppelsheim); 158, head and pronotum (iop—interior ocular puncture, pop—postocular punctures); 159, labrum; 160, male tergite 10; 161, male sternite 9; 162, aedeagus; 163, 164, median lobe (extreme shapes); 165, paramere (extreme shape)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289914/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">159</figureCitation>
).
